data.text:
Biography - OLIVER H. PARKER

Oliver H. Parker, grain buyer at Hayes and Humboldt, and a son of Lines L. Parker, of Bowdre township, was born in Vermilion county, Illinois, in the year A. D. 1860. He resides with his family in Tuscola. In 1881 he was married to Miss Angle Wallace, a daughter of Joseph and Mary Ann (Breezley) Wallace. Joseph Wallace was a pioneer settler in Bowdre township. To Mr. and Mrs. Parker were born four children: Burt I., Fred Earle, Minnie Pearle and Everett Dewey. Mr. Parker is one of the substantial business men of the county.
